OL,3,CHow a mother's campaign after the
OL,4,Cmurder of her autistic son could
OL,5,Cchange law
OL,7,FAs the Mental Health Bill returned to
OL,8,Fthe House of Commons on Monday
OL,9,Fevening, cross-party MPs urged the
OL,10,Fgovernment to back a change in law
OL,11,Fthat would allow families to request
OL,12,Fmental capacity assessments for
OL,13,Fvulnerable loved ones.
OL,15,FIt comes following years of
OL,16,Fcampaigning by Fiona Laskaris, whose
OL,17,F24-year-old son Christopher was
OL,18,Fexploited and ultimately murdered by a
OL,19,Fconvicted criminal in his own home in
OL,20,F2016.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/23
