OL,3,CHow a mother's campaign after the
OL,4,Cmurder of her autistic son could
OL,5,Cchange law
OL,7,FShe was repeatedly dismissed for years
OL,8,Fwhen she tried to get Christopher a
OL,9,Fmental capacity assessment, which
OL,10,Festablishes whether someone has the
OL,11,Fability to make decisions about their
OL,12,Fown safety and wellbeing, and helps
OL,13,Fdetermine what support they may need.
OL,14,FShe believes that if her concerns had
OL,15,Fbeen listened to, he would still be
OL,16,Falive today.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/23
