OL,3,CHow a mother's campaign after the
OL,4,Cmurder of her autistic son could
OL,5,Cchange law
OL,7,F"I obviously wouldn't release the
OL,8,Fpassport. However, the support worker
OL,9,Fwas told by the social worker team
OL,10,Fthat our daughter had assumed
OL,11,Fcapacity, so was able to make those
OL,12,Fdecisions of her own free will."
OL,14,F"No capacity assessments were carried
OL,15,Fout," he added. "We were never asked.
OL,16,FAnd they used the term 'assumed
OL,17,Fcapacity'. 'Assumed' all the time.
OL,19,F"I was in tears. Devastating to think
OL,20,Fthat that could have happened."
