OL,3,CHow a mother's campaign after the
OL,4,Cmurder of her autistic son could
OL,5,Cchange law
OL,7,FHowever, research has found that such
OL,8,Fassessments are either not carried out
OL,9,Fenough or are not carried out
OL,10,Feffectively - in particular on
OL,11,Fautistic people, adults with learning
OL,12,Fdisabilities or those with severe
OL,13,Fmental health conditions, such as
OL,14,Fbipolar and schizophrenia.
OL,16,F'Losing a child is the worst thing
OL,17,Fthat can happen to anyone, but I think
OL,18,Fa preventable death is the very
OL,19,Fworst,' Fiona Laskaris previously told
OL,20,FITV News.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G18/23
